        "id": "OCF-XXIV",
        "label": "Ordo of Louis XI",
        "labelFr": "Ordo de Louis XI",
        "openatlasClass": "E33 Linguistic Object",
        "systemClass": "artifact",
        "viewClass": "artifact",
        "type": "ordo_text",
        "tradition": "OCF",
        "date": "15 August 1461 (ceremony); 1478 (text)",
        "description": "Jean Foulquart, procureur syndic de l'échevinage of Reims, wrote in 1478 a treatise on the obligations of the échevins at ceremonies, incorporating the ordo used at Louis XI's coronation on 15 August 1461. An amalgam of the Last Capetian Ordo and the Ordo of Charles V. Rubrics translated into French, formulas left in Latin. Full text never previously published."
      }
